cs.DL, cs.IR, cs.CY, cs.CL, cs.CR

The paper describes a method and tool for identifying landmark patents in biomedical innovation by mining and analyzing cited references within large sets of patents. This involves techniques related to information retrieval (IR) and natural language processing (NLP), which are commonly used in the sub-categories of cs.DL (Digital Libraries), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), and cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper deals with patent analysis and classification, which are relevant to the sub-categories of cs.CY (Computers and Society) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
